The IMS Center researchers at Missouri S&amp;T completed a successful development of model-based diagnostics and prognostics tools and demonstrated them in LabVIEW which is a standard software product from National Instruments, a member company in the IMS Center. The tool box has been introduced and demonstrated to the company members during Industrial Advisory Board Meeting (IAB 25) and IAB 26.  This tool box is an alternative to data-driven diagnostics and prognostics schemes when significant quantities of data are not available.  A tutorial was given at the IAB 27 held at Boeing St. Louis on May 14th, 2014.  The IMS Center researchers have been developing the tools for the past 5 years and the tools have been implemented in the past year in LabVIEW. Several applications have been demonstrated with the tool box.  This tool box will be available to any IMS member company for internal use.  Discussions are being held with the National Instruments to commercialize and support the tool box.   




